##### MF33: COVARIANCES OF NEUTRON CROSS SECTIONS                 1840 1451
                                                                  1840 1451
In MF33, we store the covariances of most, but not all, reaction  1840 1451
channels that are given in MF3. All covariances are generated     1840 1451
with the TASMAN code [kon12], which generates TALYS runs using    1840 1451
a Monte Carlo parameter method.                                   1840 1451
For each MT-number, the information consists of:                  1840 1451
1. Covariances for MTa, Ea and MTa, Ea (variances)                1840 1451
2. Covariances for MTa, Ea and MTa, Eb (correlations for the      1840 1451
   same reaction channel between different energies)              1840 1451
3. Covariances for MTa, Ea and MTb, Ea (correlations between      1840 1451
   different reaction channels for the same energy)               1840 1451
4. Covariances for MTa, Ea and MTb, Eb (correlations between      1840 1451
   different reaction channels for different energies)            1840 1451
Classes 1 and 2 are covered by NI-type subsubsections with        1840 1451
flag LB=5, followed by a LB=8 section which contains              1840 1451
the cross section variances multiplied by 1.e-3. Next, classes 3  1840 1451
and 4 are covered by flag LB=6 to account for the different       1840 1451
energy grids that two correlating MT-sections may have. Since     1840 1451
the total correlation matrix is fully symmetric, we only need to  1840 1451
include the correlation elements between different MT-numbers     1840 1451
once, and we do that in the subsection with the lowest of the     1840 1451
two MT-numbers. We include covariance information for all the     1840 1451
total cross sections, the lumped partial cross sections and the   1840 1451
individual inelastic cross sections per level (MT51,...). We do   1840 1451
not include covariances for MT600 and higher MT-numbers. For the  1840 1451
most important channels, we include cross-channel correlations.   1840 1451
                                                                  1840 1451
##### MF34: COVARIANCES OF ANGULAR DISTRIBUTIONS                  1840 1451
                                                                  1840 1451
In MF34, we store the covariances of the elastic scattering       1840 1451
angular distributions that are given in MF4/MT2. All covariances  1840 1451
are generated with the TASMAN code [kon12], which generates       1840 1451
TALYS runs using a Monte Carlo parameter method. The tables are   1840 1451
restricted to MT2 and contain covariances for the first 6         1840 1451
Legendre coefficients. Both intra- and inter-correlations of the  1840 1451
various Legendre coefficients are given. As in MF33, the LB5      1840 1451
representation is used.                                           1840 1451
                                                                  1840 1451
##### MF40: COVARIANCES OF ISOMER PRODUCTION                      1840 1451
                                                                  1840 1451
For covariances of ground state and isomeric cross sections, the  1840 1451
same procedures as for MF33 are used.                             1840 1451
